feedback: Unfortunately this made me want to watch Inception and Dune (again), thanks for the 5+- hour loss.
The more information question showed several times, but I felt like there was not any more information on the screen.
Maybe it was my laptop, but the "next" button to scroll through the lists wasn't very clear

It felt like some movies/series were in an unusual category (e.g. American Horror Story in sci-fi) and that certain categories were omitted (e.g. Horror), even though that last problem could be based on my 5 preferences at the start.
When looking for "Disney", nothing came up, might be an idea to add that.
geen vragen, succes met je onderzoek!
The mobile interface wasn't working as expected, but was able to fulfill the prompts

I did not realise I had to look around actively while choosing a film/series, but found out while I was answering the questions after that I should have looked better. 

I could not really resonate with the 36 options to choose my preferences from, it was not so diverse I think. 

Cool study!
